        "content": "<p>I have a problem with the computation of Lobatto quadrature formula.<br>\nIn the second snippet of the Czech textbook they say:</p>\n<p>we directly compute <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>9.23</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(9.23)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">9.23</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> but I do not follow how did they computed <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>9.25</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(9.25)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">9.25</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> and<br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mfrac><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>A</mi><mo>ˉ</mo></mover><mi>i</mi></msub><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mn>2</mn></msup><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A_i=\\frac{\\bar{A}_i}{1-x_i}^2, i=1,...,n-1</an